objects.description:
Define apple in the real world.

Apple is a common name. The apple does not exist in the English language; it is a translation. It means "apple tree" in some languages. It also has other meanings. The name has come to be used to mean not only an apple-shaped apple, but also any product produced in the fruit that contains an apple core, i.e., apple sauce, apple butter, apple juice, apple cider, apple jelly, apple sauce,.
